dc:date  a      owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5421  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunogold localization of CBF-A (CArG-binding factor-A, gene:HNRNPAB) in EM sections of the hippocampal regions shows gold particles on both sides of excitatory synpases identified by prominent PSDs (Fig. 4E-H).. Experimental description: Figure 4 legend: \"IEM labeling of CBF-A in axons and synapses. Thin sections of adult mouse brain\nwere immunostained with the anti-CBF-A antibody SAK22.\"\n\nM&M:\n\"The guinea pig anti-CBF-A antibody SAK22 was designed against the peptide EEQPMETTGATEN located in the N terminus of both p37 and p42 CBF-A isoforms as previously described (Dean et al., 2002) and was purchased from Peptide Specialty Laboratories (Heidelberg, Germany).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2023-10-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5421" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

